---
alwaysApply: true
---
- Keep the README.md focused on high-level documentation only:
    - Overview
    - Tech stack 
    - Project structure 
    - Endpoint list (names + paths only, no full JSON examples)
    - Setup instructions
    - Test instructions 
    - Deployment URL 
    - Implementation status
    - Roles
- Do NOT include in README:
    - Full endpoint response samples
    - Large code blocks
    - Detailed data models
    - Long troubleshooting sections
    - Test output
    - Deep architectural explanations
- Create additional files for detailed documentation:
    - docs/endpoints.md → detailed endpoint documentation
    - docs/architecture.md → architecture overview
    - docs/setup.md → extended environment instructions
    - docs/troubleshooting.md → logs, error cases
- If a change introduces too much complexity for the README, move the detail to /docs and link it from README.
